This paper is about designing an effective static program analysis, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of a probabilistic model, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents a method for learning good values for hyperparameters, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and cryptography (cs.CR).
